We recommended and the Management agreed to:
Require the Municipal Engineering Office to submit a justification why the project has stagnated and was delayed by 166 days;
Strictly comply with the provisions on Contract Time Extension, page 97 of the Manual of Procedures for the Procurement of Infrastructure Projects;
Submit PAG-ASA Report on dates when requested contract extensions were due to bad weather conditions or typhoons;
Justify the payment of the 5th partial billing representing only 62.60 percent accomplishment per SWA as of October 31, 2023, despite the last approved extended contract completion being on  July 5, 2023;
Justify why Liquidated Damages were not imposed on the progress payment dated December 7, 2023 after the extended contract period on July 5, 2023, has already lapsed; and
Direct the Project-in-Charge to strictly monitor the status and implementation of the Sigma Memorial Park.

We recommended and the Management agreed to the following:
Furnish the Auditor with a copy of perfected contracts and purchase orders within five (5) working days upon approval together with the supporting documents for review:
Certified copies of invitation to observers and evidence of receipt for the bidding process conducted to procurement in Table I;
Legal, Financial, and Technical Requirements along with contract documents to ascertain compliance with the PQER;
Adhere to the posting requirements for Bid Documents, Supplemental/Bid Bulletins, Notices of Award, and Notices to Proceed in the LGU's PhilGEPS; and
Justify why a warranty security in the form of retention money or a special bank guarantee was not required.

We recommended and the Management agreed to:
Require the SDO to prepare a liquidation voucher which shall be submitted with supporting documents to the Accountant;
Require the Accountant to certify that previous cash advances have been fully liquidated;
Ascertain that cash advances are actually liquidated and that no funds remain with the DCSPGT at the end of the feeding periods;
Ascertain that the CBs of DCSPGTs are reviewed and certified by an appropriate personnel;
Observe the procurement process through Negotiated Procurement-Community Participation and establish local sources; and
Open a separate and distinct bank account for the SFP.

We recommended and the Management agreed to require:
The Accountable Officer to submit the following:
Justification for non-submission of the Notice of Loss, Request for Relief of Accountability, and related documents within the 30-day reglementary period;
Notice of Loss, Request for Relief of Accountability, and related documents per COA Memorandum No. 92-751, dated February 24, 1992:
The Municipal Accountant to review the Depreciated Replacement Cost of the four motor vehicles as of the date of the traffic incident and compare with the GSIS insurance coverage to ascertain the amount of loss of PPE and to set up the corresponding receivables from the concerned accountable officer to be collected as provided in Item 7.10 of COA Circular No. 2020-004 dated January 31, 2020;

Require the Municipal Accountant to:

Determine the acquisition dates of the PPE items and Intangibles and the dates when they were available for use; 

Determine the appropriate depreciation and amortization methods, and residual values;

Setup the contra-accounts, if still applicable, and charge to Prior Year Adjustments to record the adjustments due to errors in non-provision of the depreciation and recognize amortization/depreciation on the remaining life of the Intangible and PPE, respectively, as of the end of CY 2022; and

Provide allocation for yearly depreciation and amortization for all other assets that meet the capitalization threshold.

Require the LDRRMO to coordinate closely with the Municipal LDC in the formulation of a complete and integrated LDRRMP;

Require the Departments involved in risk reduction and management to formulate detailed programs, projects and activities and to follow the timetable in the implementation of programmed projects/activities; and

Require the Local Sanggunian to approve only appropriation for PPAs specifically defined in a manner that the brief description, location, appropriated amount, time of implementation are described for easy implementation reference and guidance.

Require BAC to submit the following for contracts awarded thru Public Bidding:

Pre-Procurement Notice and Minutes of Pre-Procurement Conference conducted;

Minutes of Pre-Bid Conference conducted on June 10, 2022;

Notification to bidders of the bids received within 7 calendar days to ensure transparency and accurate representation of the bid submission in accordance with Sec 25.7 of the IRR;

Posting in the PhilGEPS or the website of the agency the Notice of Award, Purchase Order/Contract, and Notice to Proceed pursuant to related provisions of the IRR of RA 9184; and

Required documentary requirements per Appendix A of Annex H for Small Value Procurement, particularly, Mayor’s Permit, PhilGEPS Registration, Income/Business Tax Return, and Omnibus Sworn Statement of suppliers.

Require the collectors to turn over/remit all collections daily and intact to the Liquidating Officer in compliance to Sections 26 and 31 of COA Circular No. 92-382;

Closely supervise and monitor daily collections and remittances of collecting officers;

Refrain from issuing new and unused pad of ORs unless the previously issued and used ORs and corresponding collections are remitted to the Liquidating Officer; and

Strengthen internal control over collections and remittances.

Require the Municipal Accountant:

Conduct regular reconciliation of balances per supplies ledger cards with the balances per stock cards of the supplies officer;

Record stock issuances to their appropriate expense account only upon submission of the SSMI with original copy of the RIS pursuant to Sec. 121 of NGAS, Vol. 1;

Record the issued semi-expendable properties totaling ₱2.789 million to their related expense account, if issued during the current year, and as Prior Year’s Adjustments, if issued in previous years; and

Review the Other Supplies and Materials Expense account per FS and posting per Subsidiary Ledger to ascertain the variance of ₱270,756.00;

Require the Supply Officer:

Consolidate weekly the RIS for which supplies and materials were issued using the SSMI and submit the same, with the RIS, to the Accountant for recording of the cost of supplies and materials issued; 

Conduct regular reconciliation of balances per Stock Cards with balances per Supplies Ledger Cards maintained by the Accounting Unit; and

Conduct a semestral physical count of inventory items by type and submit the results to the Inventory Committee.

Require the Human Resource Officer to review the staffing requirements of each department and recommend the hiring of qualified personnel for a regular appointment, if necessary, to regulate the employment of personnel under Job Order Contract; 

Hire only JO personnel in accordance with the necessity and urgency of the department’s needs;

Assess the individual assignments of all job order personnel to avoid redundant and duplicating work accomplishments; and

Henceforth, strictly comply with Section 76 of RA No. 7160.

Require the SWM Board to:

Allocate in the SWM program under the MENRO the appropriations for fuel and lubricants of the Garbage Truck and corresponding maintenance;

Evaluate the personnel requirement for all SWM activities and employ additional personnel, if necessary, to attain the objectives of solid waste management;

Revisit the revenue code on Garbage Fees collection and revise, if warranted, the provisions and policies that would improve garbage fees collections to sustain major SWM PPAs; and

Refrain from using the Vermi Chambers as holding areas for segregated and other wastes and restore the chambers for the production of vermi culture and organic fertilizer/soil conditioner that would fetch possible revenues for SWM.

