We recommended that the Management:
Direct the Municipal Treasurer (MT) to process the execution of Market Stall           Contracts Lease;
Direct the MT to impose the immediate payment of unpaid monthly rentals and            interests and ensure that payment of rentals are updated before the renewal of the contract is made;
Direct the Municipal Accountant to take-up uncollected rentals as receivable; and
Direct the MT to monitor strictly the implementation of the terms and conditions of the Contract especially in the prompt payment of rent and the imposition of the sanction embodied thereto.

Require the Inventory Committee to conduct a complete physical count of all PPEs owned by the Municipality and submit to the Audit Team the Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (RPCPPE);

Require the Municipal Accountant and Supply Officer to reconcile their records; and

Investigate and clear all discrepancies between the physical count and the accounting records and make the necessary adjustments and corrections.

Impose strict compliance with existing ordinances on proper waste disposal to minimize accumulation of residual wastes; 

Coordinate with other agencies or entities, government or private, which could provide assistance in the disposal of these residual wastes; and 

Exert extra effort to adopt measures on how to transfer these wastes to a long term storage or disposal facility or sanitary landfill, in compliance with Section 32 of RA 9003.

Implement promptly projects that were funded out of fund transfers;

Follow-up for the approval of the required DED and the submission of other requirements to expedite the implementation of the project; and 

Assign personnel to specifically prepare and submit the required documents to avoid similar problem in the future.

Implement projects that were funded out of fund transfers within the prescribed timelines,in accordance with the guidelines provided in DILG-DBM JMC No. 2017-3 dated May 23, 2017 and the contracts, to avoid its consequences;

Closely monitor the implementation of the projects and perform necessary actions to be taken in case of delay such as imposing liquidated damages, if warranted; and

Henceforth, furnish the Audit Team copy of the contracts within 5 days after their perfection and other reports needed in the evaluation of the project implementation.

